Statements: insulin and igf1 ( insulin like growth factor 1 ) indirectly induce mtorc1 activity by stimulating class 1 pi3k ( phosphoinositol 3-kinase ) production of pip3 ( ptdins ( 3,4,5 ) p3 ) , which induces akt kinase ( protein kinase b ) at the plasma membrane , which in turn activates mtorc1 by inhibiting tsc ( tuberous sclerosis complex ) proteins 1/2 , thereby relieving their repression of rheb [ 28 ] .
